9mobile said it has upgraded its MiFi and router offering to give its customers more options to browse the internet. Customers can now get up to 380GB, plus a free router device valid for one year, and up to 200GB, plus a free MiFi device also valid for one year, the company said at a virtual launch recently. MiFi devices can be connected to a cellular network to provide internet services for up to ten devices, while routers can be connected to a cellular network to provide internet services for up to 30 devices, the telecom company said. Commenting on the offers at their virtual unveiling on Tuesday, Chief Commercial Officer, 9mobile, Stjepan Udovicic, disclosed that it demonstrated 9mobile`s commitment to boosting individuals and businesses with affordable data connectivity. “We are committed to providing affordable offerings, especially as COVID-19 has altered the world of work. Nowadays, more people are working remotely as they need affordable data to deliver their tasks and stay connected online with colleagues and business associates. Our refreshed MiFi and Router offers will see our customers enjoying more for less. For instance, a customer gets a 20GB instant sign-up data bonus, and additional 15GB data every month for 12months, plus a free MiFi device”, Udovicic said. Also, customers will get 30GB instant sign-up data bonus, and additional 20GB every month for 12months, plus a free Router device, he added.